{"pageProps":{"content":{"html":"        <h1>Use TestCafe with Gulp</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are using Gulp to organize your build process,\r\nyou can easily integrate TestCafe into the workflow.</p>\r\n<p>Suppose you have a project that uses Gulp.js to run build tasks. To integrate TestCafe into the project, go through these steps.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href=\"#step-1---install-testcafe-gulp-plugin\">Step 1 - Install TestCafe Gulp Plugin</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"#step-2---create-a-testcafe-gulp-task\">Step 2 - Create a TestCafe Gulp Task</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"#step-3---run-the-testcafe-task\">Step 3 - Run the TestCafe Task</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2 id=\"step-1---install-testcafe-gulp-plugin__$\"><a class=\"anchor-fix\" href=\"#step-1---install-testcafe-gulp-plugin\" id=\"step-1---install-testcafe-gulp-plugin\"></a>Step 1 - Install TestCafe Gulp Plugin<a class=\"anchor-hash\" href=\"#step-1---install-testcafe-gulp-plugin\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" fill=\"none\"><path d=\"M12.586 2.586a2 2 0 112.828 2.828l-3 3a2 2 0 01-2.828 0 1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414 4 4 0 005.656 0l3-3a4 4 0 00-5.656-5.656l-1.5 1.5a1 1 0 101.414 1.414l1.5-1.5zm-5 5a2 2 0 012.828 0 1 1 0 101.414-1.414 4 4 0 00-5.656 0l-3 3a4 4 0 105.656 5.656l1.5-1.5a1 1 0 10-1.414-1.414l-1.5 1.5a2.002 2.002 0 01-3.438-1.407 2 2 0 01.61-1.42l3-3z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></a></h2>\r\n<p>To install the <a href=\"https://github.com/DevExpress/gulp-testcafe\" target=\"_blank\">TestCafe Gulp plugin<span class=\"svg-no-wrap\">&#65279;<svg fill=\"none\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path d=\"M10 6H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v10a2 2 0 002 2h10a2 2 0 002-2v-4M14 4h6m0 0v6m0-6L10 14\"></path></svg></span></a>,\r\nexecute the following command from your projectâ€™s root directory.</p>\r\n<pre><code class=\"lang-sh\">npm install --save-dev gulp-testcafe\r\n</code></pre><h2 id=\"step-2---create-a-testcafe-gulp-task__$\"><a class=\"anchor-fix\" href=\"#step-2---create-a-testcafe-gulp-task\" id=\"step-2---create-a-testcafe-gulp-task\"></a>Step 2 - Create a TestCafe Gulp Task<a class=\"anchor-hash\" href=\"#step-2---create-a-testcafe-gulp-task\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" fill=\"none\"><path d=\"M12.586 2.586a2 2 0 112.828 2.828l-3 3a2 2 0 01-2.828 0 1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414 4 4 0 005.656 0l3-3a4 4 0 00-5.656-5.656l-1.5 1.5a1 1 0 101.414 1.414l1.5-1.5zm-5 5a2 2 0 012.828 0 1 1 0 101.414-1.414 4 4 0 00-5.656 0l-3 3a4 4 0 105.656 5.656l1.5-1.5a1 1 0 10-1.414-1.414l-1.5 1.5a2.002 2.002 0 01-3.438-1.407 2 2 0 01.61-1.42l3-3z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></a></h2>\r\n<p>Open <code>Gulpfile.js</code> and add a task that runs TestCafe tests.</p>\r\n<pre><code class=\"lang-js\">const gulp     = require(&#39;gulp&#39;);\r\nconst testcafe = require(&#39;gulp-testcafe&#39;);\r\n\r\ngulp.task(&#39;run-testcafe-tests&#39;, () =&gt; {\r\n    return gulp\r\n        .src(&#39;tests/test.js&#39;)\r\n        .pipe(testcafe({ browsers: [&#39;chrome&#39;, &#39;firefox&#39;] }));\r\n});\r\n</code></pre><p>This task runs tests from the <code>tests/test.js</code> file in Chrome and Firefox.</p>\r\n<p>For a complete API Reference, see <a href=\"https://github.com/DevExpress/gulp-testcafe#gulp-testcafe\" target=\"_blank\">the plugin page<span class=\"svg-no-wrap\">&#65279;<svg fill=\"none\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path d=\"M10 6H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v10a2 2 0 002 2h10a2 2 0 002-2v-4M14 4h6m0 0v6m0-6L10 14\"></path></svg></span></a>.</p>\r\n<h2 id=\"step-3---run-the-testcafe-task__$\"><a class=\"anchor-fix\" href=\"#step-3---run-the-testcafe-task\" id=\"step-3---run-the-testcafe-task\"></a>Step 3 - Run the TestCafe Task<a class=\"anchor-hash\" href=\"#step-3---run-the-testcafe-task\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" fill=\"none\"><path d=\"M12.586 2.586a2 2 0 112.828 2.828l-3 3a2 2 0 01-2.828 0 1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414 4 4 0 005.656 0l3-3a4 4 0 00-5.656-5.656l-1.5 1.5a1 1 0 101.414 1.414l1.5-1.5zm-5 5a2 2 0 012.828 0 1 1 0 101.414-1.414 4 4 0 00-5.656 0l-3 3a4 4 0 105.656 5.656l1.5-1.5a1 1 0 10-1.414-1.414l-1.5 1.5a2.002 2.002 0 01-3.438-1.407 2 2 0 01.61-1.42l3-3z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></a></h2>\r\n<p>Run this task through the command line.</p>\r\n<pre><code class=\"lang-sh\">gulp run-testcafe-tests\r\n</code></pre><div class=\"NOTE\"><p class=\"alert-title\">Note</p><p>Gulp must be installed globally to run tasks from the command line.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>Alternatively, you can create and run a dependent task.</p>\r\n<pre><code class=\"lang-js\">gulp.task(&#39;publish&#39;, [&#39;run-testcafe-tests&#39;], () =&gt; {\r\n    /* ... */\r\n});\r\n</code></pre>","headers":[{"title":"Step 1 - Install TestCafe Gulp Plugin","tagName":"h2","id":"step-1---install-testcafe-gulp-plugin","lvl":2},{"title":"Step 2 - Create a TestCafe Gulp Task","tagName":"h2","id":"step-2---create-a-testcafe-gulp-task","lvl":2},{"title":"Step 3 - Run the TestCafe Task","tagName":"h2","id":"step-3---run-the-testcafe-task","lvl":2}],"title":"Use TestCafe with Gulp","schema":null,"author":null,"preview":null,"description":null,"published":null},"topicUid":"402796","headerNav":{"items":[{"name":"TestCafe Studio","id":"TestCafe Studio"},{"name":"Guides","id":"402634","url":"/documentation/402634/guides","headerUrl":"/documentation/402635/guides/overview/getting-started","items":[]},{"name":"API","id":"402632","url":"/documentation/402632/api","items":[]},{"name":"Recipes","id":"402633","url":"/documentation/402633/recipes","items":[]},{"name":"Examples","id":"402637","url":"/documentation/402637/examples"},{"name":"FAQ","id":"403936","url":"/documentation/403936/faq","headerUrl":"/documentation/402636/faq/general-info","items":[]},{"name":"What's New","id":"What's New","url":"/release-notes","href":"/release-no